      <title>富人的挥霍导致日本零售股两极分化</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-28/splurging-by-the-wealthy-is-polarizing-japan-s-retail-stocks</link>
      <description><![CDATA[尽管通胀环境严峻，日本百货商店运营商仍受益于富裕购物者增加支出，而由于人们对购买必需品变得更加挑剔，低端零售商的表现不佳。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-28/splurging-by-the-wealthy-is-polarizing-japan-s-retail-stocks</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Jul 2024 22:00:33 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>澳大利亚准备制定严格的气候规则，企业陷入“瘫痪”</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-28/companies-paralyzed-as-australia-prepares-tough-climate-rules</link>
      <description><![CDATA[澳大利亚计划出台严格的气候信息披露规定，此举引发了企业对该国合规性的担忧，该国是全球人均排放量最大的国家之一。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-28/companies-paralyzed-as-australia-prepares-tough-climate-rules</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 28 Jul 2024 22:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
